      <p>I&#39;m finally getting around to reading this blog from the beginning, and though I&#39;m a couple of years late, holy freaking COW. I started off reading the tasting menu sitting straight up in my office chair, looking for all intents and purposes like I was reading some very important, completely work related document. Somewhere around the fourth course, I noticed my chin was of it&#39;s own volition propped heavily on my left hand. Only towards the very end when I kid you not, my entire mid section sort of collapsed on me and sent me slumping down in my chair, elliciting a raised eyebrow from my boss, did I snap out of it and back to &#8220;I&#39;m totally working over here, ALL the time&#8221; attention. Time to go check ticket prices on Virgin America. At home, on my own time, of COURSE.</p>
